    base:desc "Control commands originate from the Digital Twin’s Control Panel User Interface FE and are routed via the internal ROS 2 network to the vehicle’s on‑board actuator interfaces (Motor Actuation FE, Steering Actuation FE, Servo Actuation FE). The Data Translation component performs unit conversion and aligns the command messages before they are transmitted over the Wi‑Fi link to the vehicle’s firmware. Commands are packaged as structured ROS 2 messages containing target positions, velocities or torque values and are validated against safety limits defined in the Control FE. No explicit authentication or encryption is described; conflict resolution relies on the firmware’s priority scheme for actuator commands. Confirmation of command execution is obtained through downstream telemetry feeds consumed by the Data Collection FE, which updates the vehicle state displayed in the 3‑D visualization."
