    base:desc "The Digital Twin system employs a hierarchical networking layout. Inter‑software‑component communication takes place on a ROS 2 publish/subscribe network that operates over UDP, while inter‑entity communication (between Physical Twin, Digital Twin and User interfaces) is conducted over a Wi‑Fi radio link using UDP. The topology can be considered a bus‑like architecture radiating from a Wi‑Fi access point. Bandwidth requirements are driven by the high‑rate LiDAR point‑cloud stream, though exact values are not specified; latency is expected to be low enough for real‑time visualization but quantitative figures are not provided. Reliability and redundancy mechanisms, as well as explicit security protocols (e.g., TLS, VPN, authentication), are not detailed in the document."
