    base:desc "Integration with external systems is achieved through ROS 2’s DDS‑based publish/subscribe middleware, which conforms to the RTI‑DDS or Cyclone‑DDS profiles common in automotive software stacks. The Digital Twin packages exchange messages over standard ROS 2 topic conventions (e.g., `/sensor/pointcloud`, `/actuator/command`) enabling interoperability with other ROS 2‑based Digital Twins or enterprise middleware that adheres to ROS 2/IPsec and related security standards. Time synchronization across devices leverages the ROS 2 Time API, which itself relies on the underlying system clock synchronization mechanisms mandated by ISO 23247 and automotive safety standards."
