]

instance security_and_safety_considerations : DTDFVocab:SecuritySafety [
    base:desc "ISO 26262-1:2018 defines the functional safety lifecycle for automotive electronic systems, requiring a systematic risk assessment, determination of the appropriate Automotive Safety Integrity Level (ASIL), definition of safety goals, and implementation of safety mechanisms such as redundancy, fault detection, and fail-safe behaviours. ISO 15622:2018 specifies performance and test procedures for Adaptive Cruise Control (ACC) systems, including safety-critical test scenarios (e.g., detection delays, braking response times, longitudinal control accuracy) that must satisfy the ASIL levels assigned by ISO 26262. 3GPP TS 22.185 v15.0.0, a service requirements specification for V2X communication, prescribes cybersecurity measures for v2x services, such as authentication via digital certificates, TLS-based encryption, message integrity checks, and anti-spoofing techniques, alongside access-control policies to protect vehicle‑to‑vehicle and vehicle‑to‑infrastructure data exchanges. Together, these standards provide a framework for designing and validating safe, secure digital twin components for intelligent transport systems."
]
